Others: Yamamoto allowed four runs in three innings, marking only the third time he failed to see north of four innings across 17 starts in 2024.
Mookie Betts hit his 19th home run of the campaign, marking his second homer in as many days.
Shohei Ohtani hit another home run and collected two stolen bases, inching closer to the 60-60 club with 53 home runs and 55 stolen bases.
The Dodgers can look forward to a pair of three-game sets against the San Diego Padres and the Rockies again to end the 2024 campaign.
